  { question: "How much self-employment tax do I owe on side hustle income?", answer: "Self-employment tax is 15.3% of 92.35% of your net self-employment income. This covers Social Security (12.4%) and Medicare (2.9%). Only 92.35% of net earnings are taxable because the IRS allows you to deduct the employer-equivalent portion. For example, if your net profit is $40,000, your SE tax would be approximately $40,000 x 0.9235 x 0.153 = $5,652." },
  { question: "What business expenses can I deduct from my side hustle?", answer: "Common deductible expenses include home office costs, equipment and supplies, software subscriptions, internet and phone bills (business portion), vehicle mileage for business trips, advertising, professional services, and continuing education. Keep detailed records and receipts for all business expenses to substantiate your deductions." },
