  { question: "How do I calculate my effective hourly rate from a side hustle?", answer: "Divide your annual take-home pay (after all taxes) by the total hours you work per year. For example, if you take home $20,000 annually and work 15 hours per week, your effective rate is $20,000 / (15 x 52) = $25.64 per hour. This gives a realistic picture of what your time is actually worth after taxes and expenses." },
